      },
      "date": "2015-08-07 14:47:07.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nI personally like to see the user land code move to the PRIx defined in inttypes.h instead of Lustre's home brewed libcfs types.h.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "ffd313b1058384f102e32a229c8ca00775c1a7fd",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 419,
        "name": "Frank Zago",
        "email": "fzago@cray.com",
        "username": "fzago.cray"
      },
      "date": "2015-08-07 14:58:16.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> I personally like to see the user land code move to the PRIx\n > defined in inttypes.h instead of Lustre's home brewed libcfs\n > types.h.\n\nIMO, PRIx macros are no better than the Lustre LPU/LPX ones. I think the patch is fine as-is.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "fe165147e29e5dbb4dc04cf2e04e61fd720ab35e",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2015-08-08 08:09:57.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nJames, this patch is removing Lustre-specific type usage, so it isn't clear that this is the right place for your objection?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "95246ae1730c10c6152137944424e369ff2dd934",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 125,
        "name": "James Simmons",
        "email": "jsimmons@infradead.org",
        "username": "jsimmons"
      },
      "date": "2015-08-09 20:06:45.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nThe question is a direct %lld replacement the right choice for both 32 bit and 64 bit environments. Hammond what is your opinion in this case? I remember having discussing before with you about this.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "7059f9ded9e3d42b82abffe41a72628eba878e2a",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 177,
        "name": "John Hammond",
        "email": "jhammond@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jhammond"
      },
      "date": "2015-08-10 14:54:26.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nIn userspace when printing __u64 or similar we should use ll[dux] with an explicit cast to long long or unsigned long long.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
